      • setStatusFailed

        public static void setStatusFailed(List<? extends Pe> peList,
                                   int hostId,
                                   boolean failed)
        Sets the status of PEs of a host to FAILED or FREE. NOTE: hostId are used for debugging purposes, which is ON by default. Use setStatusFailed(List, boolean) if you do not want this information.
        Parameters:
        peList - the host's PE list to be set as failed or free
        hostId - the id of the host
        failed - true if the host's PEs have to be set as FAILED, false if they have to be set as FREE.
        See Also:
        setStatusFailed(java.util.List, boolean)
